      <h1 class='title'>Renewable Energy Bill</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='lords-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 18 January 2005 vol 668 c26WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_26ws' title='Col. 26WS &mdash; HL Deb 18 January 2005 vol 668 c26WS' name='column_26ws' href='#column_26ws' rel='bookmark'>26WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0668P0-05312'>
        <a name='S5LV0668P0_20050118_LWS_10'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-david-triesman' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0668P0_20050118_LWS_10' title='Link to this speech by Mr David Triesman' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-david-triesman" title="Mr David Triesman">Lord Triesman</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S5LV0668P0-05312">Speaking in the House during the Second Reading debate of the <a href="/bills/renewable-energy-bill">Renewable Energy Bill</a> on Friday 14 January 2005, I mistakenly said (<span class="italic">Official Report</span>, col. 488) that there had been an improvement of 80 per cent in the economic efficiency of wind energy generation "in the past two years".</p><p id="S5LV0668P0-05313">The economic efficiency gain was achieved in fact over 20 years. I apologise for this mistake and have taken the earliest opportunity to correct it.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
